<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,620,645]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[504,648,620,645]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.325" metricValueMax="1.55" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="13.25" valueMax="15.5" valueMin="11.0">11–15.5 mm</quantity>
; setation of head, pronotum, and ventral side mixed yellow and black, that of elytra almost completely black; antennomeres reddish, VIII–XI almost brown-orange, antennomere III less than 
<number box="[207,242,692,717]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as IV, apical antennomeres only slightly widened, XI ca. twice as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[1317,1399,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1538,1560]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,949,1514]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[167,1419,943,1522]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 18. Mylabris (M.) madoni Marseul: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286159/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[1371,1399,692,716]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
A); pronotum without fore transverse depression; elytral black pattern (
<figureCitation box="[946,1031,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1538,1560]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,949,1514]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[167,1419,943,1522]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 18. Mylabris (M.) madoni Marseul: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286159/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[1003,1031,728,752]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
B) without apical fascia, with two subequal sub-rounded spots on basal third, one middle greatly sinuous narrow fascia and one subapical bisinuate wider fascia; mesosternum as in 
<figureCitation box="[523,604,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1538,1560]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,949,1514]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[167,1419,943,1522]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 18. Mylabris (M.) madoni Marseul: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286159/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[575,604,800,824]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
C; male gonoforceps slender in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1115,1196,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1538,1560]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,949,1514]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[167,1419,943,1522]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 18. Mylabris (M.) madoni Marseul: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286159/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[1168,1196,800,824]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
E), fused ventrally in basal half (
<figureCitation box="[275,357,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1538,1560]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,949,1514]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[167,1419,943,1522]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 18. Mylabris (M.) madoni Marseul: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286159/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[328,357,836,860]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
D); distal hook of aedeagus relatively close to apex, proximal hook relatively far from the distal one (
<figureCitation box="[206,288,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1538,1560]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,949,1514]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[167,1419,943,1522]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 18. Mylabris (M.) madoni Marseul: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286159/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[259,288,872,896]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
